  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients 18 years of age or older

          -  Patients with no known hemorrhage risk, with an indication of endobronchial biopsy

          -  Patients with no contra-indication for bronchial endoscopy

          -  Patients with or without endobronchial tumors

          -  Patients who have provided written informed consent

          -  Patients with health insurance coverage

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Refusal to be examined

          -  Contraindication for electrocoagulation (Pacemaker or metallic endobronchial
             prosthesis)

          -  Pregnant women

          -  Patients unable to provide voluntary informed consent, under (tutelage) or
             guardianship, or unable to come to the center
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
